title: House votes to provide money for highways, transit
text:
Apartment Sales Tracker Home / Nation & World / House votes to provide money for highways, transit The U.S. House of Representatives passed a bill that would extend spending authority for transportation programs through Oct. 29, and replenish the federal Highway Trust Fund with $8 billion. In this photo, afternoon rush hour traffic moves along a highway in Phoenix. (AP file photo) House votes to provide money for highways, transit By: The Associated Press July 29, 2015 5:53 pm 0 In one of their last decisions before adjourning for a month, the House backed a bill that would extend spending authority for transportation programs through Oct. 29, and replenish the federal Highway Trust Fund with $8 billion.
